div.h1: Domain Event Struct Memory Layout (amd64 Go)
div.p: String header = 16 bytes (ptr 8B + len 8B) time.Time = 24 bytes (wall 8B + ext 8B + loc ptr 8B) [16]byte = 16 bytes Cache line = 64 B (dashed) Page boundary = 4096 B (bold)

String payload (actual character bytes) lives on the heap, not in the struct. These layouts show header bytes only stack/inline allocation of the struct value. ExpiresAt *time.Time in URLCreatedEvent: 8 bytes (pointer), pointed-to value on heap.
Total: 136 bytes = 0x88 Spans 3 cache lines (063, 64127, 128135+) Largest alignment: 8 bytes (pointer) struct align = 8 No internal padding required (all fields naturally aligned)

g.text: 0x38 EventID string +16 B (UUID v4 dedup key)
0x68 IPHash string +16 B (SHA-256 hex; never raw IP)

div.p: Total: 160 bytes = 0xA0 Spans 3 full cache lines (063, 64127, 128159) No padding: all fields are 8-byte aligned Referer omitempty JSON omitted when len==0; struct field always present
Total: 96 bytes = 0x60 Spans 2 cache lines (063, 6495) Smallest of the four event types No padding; all fields naturally 8-byte aligned
Total: 128 bytes = 0x80 Spans exactly 2 cache lines (063, 64127) int on amd64 = 8 bytes; int64 = 8 bytes No padding anywhere; perfect 8-byte alignment throughout
